The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Stock-taking

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Sept. 1: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh today reviewed the global oil price situation with senior officials of the petroleum ministry. The officials, led by petroleum secretary S.C. Tripathy, emphasised the need to revamp local oil prices. They argued that if oil prices are not increased, oil PSUs would sink deeper into losses. 




